                      AvailableCards availableCards,
                      TypeOfAction typeOfAction,

                      BoardCoord lastSelectedCell,
                      boolean noOption)
        Method that needs to be called after the controller is instantiated (you can choose between two different configure methods). Manages everything to show
        Parameters:
        client - reference to the Client instance
        boardController - reference to the boardController instance
        availableCards - availableCards message
        typeOfAction - typeOfAction in which the player is involved
        images - List of images to show
        lastSelectedCell - BoardCoord of the last selected cell in the screen (needed if the typeOfAction is a GRAB)
        noOption - false if the player must choose

      • configure

        public void configure(Client client,
                      BoardController boardController,
                      AvailableCards availableCards,
                      java.util.List<javafx.scene.image.Image> images,
                      BoardCoord lastSelectedCell,
                      java.util.List<javafx.scene.image.ImageView> myWeapons)
        Method that needs to be called after the controller is instantiated (you can choose between two different configure methods). This method has to be called if the player has already 3 weapons and the type of message is a GRAB. Manages everything to show and the discard of a weapon.
        Parameters:
        client - reference to the Client instance
        boardController - reference to the boardController instance
        availableCards - availableCards message
        images - List of images to show
        lastSelectedCell - BoardCoord of the last selected cell in the screen (needed if the typeOfAction is a GRAB)
        myWeapons - List of the ImageViews of the weapons of the player of the client
